  "title": "Add active refinements info for the menu, hierarchicalMenu and the refinementList widgets ",
  "body": "Would be great to add more info in the markup about the active. That would help to build UI/UX where the list of those possible filter items are hidden.\n\nWe could for instance imagine to have:\n- add a class at the top level that there is 1 or more items selected\n- add a count value in the `ais-menu--header` to indicate how many items have been selected (+ extra attribute, to get that value easily accessible programmatically)\n\n![pasted image at 2016_05_05 23_26](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1101220/15152209/af404e30-16d4-11e6-9265-88bf6dae3a4a.png)\n\n``` html\n<div data-reactroot=\"\" class=\"ais-root ais-menu\">\n  <div class=\"ais-menu--header ais-header ais-menu__active\" data-active-items=\"1\">\n    Cuisine <span class=\"ais-header-active--count\">1</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"ais-body ais-menu--body\">\n     ...\n```\n\nWhat do you guys think?\n",
  "created_at": "2016-05-10T16:54:04Z",
